6.20	Port_Elizabeth,_South_Africa	Port Elizabeth	Port Elizabeth (Xhosa: ; colloquial The Bay or Afrikaans: ) is one of the largest cities in South Africa, situated in the Eastern Cape Province, 770 km (478 mi) east of Cape Town. The city, often shortened to PE and nicknamed "The Friendly City" or "The Windy City", stretches for 16 km along Algoa Bay, and is one of the major seaports in South Africa. It is also referred to as Africa's Watersport Capital.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Nelson_Mandela_Stadium_in_Port_Elizabeth.jpg/250px-Nelson_Mandela_Stadium_in_Port_Elizabeth.jpg
